&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CONSULTANT OPHTHALMOLOGIST (3Posts) WITH A SPECIAL INTEREST IN MEDICAL RETINA &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3 Substantive Consultant Posts&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Manchester Royal Eye Hospital wishes to invite applications for three Consultant Ophthalmologist positions with a special interest in Medical Retina. The award-winning team currently comprises of 11 consultants with a wide variety of clinical and research interests including developing pharmaceutical and genetic therapies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Consultants will provide a sub-specialty expertise in medical retina which is currently based on a hub and spoke configuration on five sites around the city and centered at the Manchester Royal Eye Hospital on the Oxford Road Campus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would welcome enquiries and applications from those whose expertise may extend beyond medical retina and wish also to work within complementary subspecialties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful candidates if they wish would have the opportunity to undertake cataract surgery at our specialist cataract centre at Withington Community Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should have Fellowship of the Royal College of Ophthalmologists or equivalent. These are offered as full-time posts but applications will be considered from those who for personal reasons cannot work full-time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have full registration with the GMC at the time of application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have entry on the GMC Specialist Register via one of the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1) Certificate of Completion of Training (CCT)&lt;br /&gt;(The proposed CCT date must be within 6 months of the interview)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2) Certificate of Eligibility for Specialist Registration (CESR)&lt;br /&gt;(CESR Candidates must have written GMC confirmation at the time of application)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMs Romi ChhabraJob titleClinical Lead for Medical RetinaEmail addressromi.chhabra@mft.nhs.ukAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
